@page "/panel/overview"

<h2>Panel / Overview</h2>
<div class="sample-block" id="panel-overview">
    <IntegralUIPanel ContentAlignment="IntegralUIContentAlignment.MiddleCenter" Size="@ctrlSize">
        <div style="background:#dedede;border:thin solid #808080;padding: 25px;">Sample Content Block</div>
    </IntegralUIPanel>
    <div class="feature-help">
        <p><span class="initial-space"></span><strong><span class="code-name">IntegralUI</span> Panel</strong> is a Blazor Component that represents a generic container with option for content alignment.</p>
        <p><span class="initial-space"></span>Whenever Panel resize, its content position is auto-updated, based on current alignment set. Scrollbars will appear automatically, when content size exceeds the Panel size.</p>
        <p><span class="initial-space"></span>The following properties and events are supported:</p>
        <ul class="feature-points">
            <li><span class="code-name">ColorScheme</span> - Specifies the the current color scheme in use: Light or Dark</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">ContentAlignment</span> - Specifies the alignment of content inside the Panel</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">Data</span> - Specifies an object that holds data related to the component</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">Enabled</span> - Determines whether the component is enabled or disabled</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">Name</span> - Uniquely identifies the component</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">ScrollAppearance</span> - Specifies the scrollbar appearance: Static or Dynamic</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">State</span> - Specifies the component state: Normal or Selected.</li>
            <li class="feature-points-break"><br /></li>
            <li><span class="code-name">EnabledChanged</span> - Occurs when Enabled property changes</li>
            <li><span class="code-name">StateChanged</span> - Occurs when State property changes</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    public IntegralUISize ctrlSize = new() { Height = 300 };

}
